Unique project in Cox's Bazar puts Bangladeshi and refugee women first,
provides skills

   A new training project in southeast Bangladesh to promote self-reliance
   among women in communities hosting refugees as well as among Rohingya
   refugee women has become operational in Cox's Bazar. The project is
   potentially a game-changer for women in these communities. It is being
   supported by UNHCR, the UN Refugee Agency.    Et aussi

